Exorbitant price at a food court - might be due to the rental. Decided to give them a try given that their main outlet has good reviews.
Food was a sore disappointment though. Ordered the chicken buah keluak udon at $11. Chicken portion was pathetic with a hard boiled egg and a small bowl of udon. Chicken wasn't flavorful and when mixed in with the wet udon, it tasted diluted.
Taste wasn't good, portion wasn't enough. Expensive.
abit overpriced but food is good.
